meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 1. to pull; to tug; to lead (e.g. a horse) カーテンがゆっくり引かれた。The curtains were drawn slowly.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 2. to draw (attention, sympathy, etc.); to attract (e.g. interest) See also 惹く ひく, See also 注意を引く

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 3. to draw back (e.g. one's hand); to draw in (one's chin, stomach, etc.); to pull in あんな本みたらフツーの女は引くもんな！Obviously a normal woman would lose interest if she saw a book like that!

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 4. to draw (a card, mahjong tile, etc.) あなたの引いたカードは赤のマークですね。The card you drew was a red, wasn't it?

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 5. to draw (a line, plan, etc.) See also 図面を引くＡからＢまで線をひきなさい。Draw a line from A to B.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 6. to catch (a cold) See also 風邪を引く悪い風邪をひいていて、さらに悪いことには、雪が降ってきました。I had a bad cold, and to make matters worse, it began snowing.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 7. to play (a stringed or keyboard instrument) See also 弾く ひく彼女はグランドピアノでその曲を引いた。She played that tune on her grand piano.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 8. to look up (in a dictionary, phone book, etc.); to consult; to check See also 辞書を引くその単語を辞書でひいてごらん。Look up the word in your dictionary.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 9. to haul; to pull (vehicles) esp. 牽く私は馬が荷車を引いているのを見た。I saw a horse pulling a cart.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 10. to subtract; to deduct １０から２を引くと、８残る。Two from ten leaves eight.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 11. to recede; to ebb; to fade 腫れが引くまで何日くらいかかりますか。How many days will it take until the swelling goes down?

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 12. to be descend from; to inherit (a characteristic) その作家はギリシャの王家の血統を引いていた。The writer was descended from the Greek royal family.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 13. to quote; to cite; to raise (as evidence) できるだけ英語から例をひこう。Insofar as possible, our examples will be drawn from English.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 14. to lay on (electricity, gas, etc.); to install (e.g. a telephone); to supply (e.g. water) 海底ケーブルが両国の間に引かれた。A submarine cable was laid between the two countries.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 15. to hold (e.g. a note)

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 16. to apply (e.g. lipstick); to oil (e.g. a pan); to wax (e.g. a floor)

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Intransitive verb
meanings.meaning: 17. to move back; to draw back; to recede; to fall back; to retreat also written as 退く

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Intransitive verb
meanings.meaning: 18. to lessen; to subside; to ebb; to go down (e.g. of swelling) also written as 退く

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'ku' ending, Intransitive verb
meanings.meaning: 19. to resign; to retire; to quit also written as 退く
